{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox football biography | name = John Anderson | fullname = John Curr Anderson<ref>{{Hugman|345}}</ref> | birth_date = 8 May 1915 | birth_place = [[Dundee]], Scotland | death_date = February 1987 (aged 71) | death_place = [[Portsmouth]], England | currentclub = | position = [[Centre forward]] | youthyears1= | youthclubs1= [[Stobswood F.C.|Stobswood]] | years1 = 1933–1946 | years2 =1946–1947 | clubs1 = [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] | clubs2 =[[Aldershot F.C.|Aldershot]] | caps1 = 80 | goals1 = 36 | caps2 = 4 | goals2 = 1 | nationalyears1= | nationalteam1= | nationalcaps1= | nationalgoals1 = | ntupdate = | pcupdate = }} '''John Curr Anderson''' (8 May 1915 &ndash; February 1987) was a Scottish professional [[association football|footballer]], who played as a [[centre forward]]. The summit of his career was scoring one of the goals for Portsmouth in their 4–1 win over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in the [[1939 FA Cup Final]].
He was the second John Anderson to play for Portsmouth, the [[John Anderson (footballer born 1878)|first]] having joined the club in 1903.
